tp:treatment-sec.p:
Head.
Longer than wide; lateral margins of head sinuous; mandibular plates longer than clypeus, each rounded apically, inner margins ahead of clypeus contiguous; antenniferous tubercles visible in dorsal view (
Fig. 9
). Each antenniferous tubercle with lateral and ventral processes (
Fig. 12
). Each antennomere I not reaching head apically; each antennomere II longer than the remaining antennomeres together; each antennomere IV wider in the basal half than in the apical half, basal half glabrous, apical half setose (
Fig. 11
); each antennomere V entirely setose; proportion of antennomeres II>IV>V>I>III. Proportion of labiomeres II>III>I=IV.

Thorax.
Pronotum about two times and a half wider than long; each anterior margin concave; each anterolateral angle bearing a minute process; each anterolateral margin slightly concave; humeri broadly rounded; each posterolateral margin sinuous; posterior margin straight (
Fig. 9
). Apical angle of each corium reaching abdominal segment VI; membranes not surpassing abdominal margin posteriorly; membranes hyaline, with grayish maculae (
Figs 2
, 
9
). Evaporatorium surrounding peritreme on each metepisternum and restricted to spiracle margin on each mesepimeron (
Fig. 13
). Tibiae sulcate dorsally.

Male genitalia.
Pygophore rectangular in dorsal view, wider than long (
Fig. 14
). Genital cup opened posterodorsally, genital cup striate (
Figs 14-15
). Dorsal rim (
dr
) corrugate, with microtrichia; superior ridge (
sr
) convex, produced posteriorly. Posterolateral angles of pygophore produced posteriorly, rounded. Ventral rim concave in ventral view (
Fig. 16
); infoldings of ventral rim robust, produced dorsally, U-shaped medially (
Fig. 15
); densely punctate. Segment X almost twice as long as wide, with a less sclerotized median line (
Fig. 15
). Crown of parameres (
p
) directed dorsally (
Fig. 17
), crown apically rounded and placed at an oblique angle to stem; lateral margin bearing scale-like microsculptures (
Fig. 17
). Phallotheca (
ph
) twice as long as wide (
Figs 18–20
); phallotheca smooth; vesica (
v
) blade-like, surrounded by membranous conjunctiva (
cj
); ductus seminis distalis (
dsd
) shorter than vesica, its apex bent ventrally (
Figs 18–20
).

Female genitalia.
Gonocoxites VIII (gc8) tumid, as long as wide, facing posteriorly (
Figs 21–22
); mesial margins straight, juxtaposed; posterior margin convex; mesial and posterior margins setose (
Fig. 21
). Gonocoxites IX (
gc9
) flat, twice as wide as long; anterior margin concave. Laterotergites VIII (
la8
) triangular; posterior margin smooth; spiracle present. Laterotergites IX (
la9
) flat, blunt apically, not surpassing tergite VIII. Segment X rectangular, longer than wide. Gonapophyses IX (
g9
) with 1+1 triangular sclerotized areas, placed along with elliptical chitinellipsen (
ch
) (
Fig. 23
). Median duct of vesicular area (
va
) conical; 
ductus receptaculi
distal (
drd
) ¾ as long as vesicular area; posterior annular flange (
paf
) wider than anterior annular flange (
aaf
); 
capsula seminalis
(
cs
) globose, with one process (
Fig. 23
).
